The paper deals with a distributed computing problem of reconciling sets of keys held by multiple parties in a cloud-based setting. The problem is algorithmic in nature and involves efficient communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also uses network coding techniques and IBLTs, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The problem of set reconciliation is also relevant to networking (cs.NI) and systems (cs.SY) research.
